<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n09095a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n09" href="#n09095a">N09 (VI.B.1)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n09all.htm#n09095a"> 95(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> pride &mdash; war &mdash; caruse / avarice &mdash; commerce &mdash; wealth / ambition &mdash; politics &mdash; wisdom </blockquote> <dd class="well"><mm class="note">Note: <cite>New Science</cite> 132: Out of ferocity, avarice, and ambition, the three vices which run throughout the human race, it <font color="green">[legislation]</font> creates the military, merchant, and governing classes, and thus the strength, riches, and wisdom of commonwealths. Out of these three vices, which could certainly destroy all mankind on the face of the earth, it makes civil happiness. </mm> </dd></dl>
